# Commit Message Conventions

When creating commit messages (`git commit -m "..."`), always use conventional commit prefixes.

## Prefixes

| Prefix  | Purpose | Example |
| :------ | :------ | :------ |
| build   | Changes to build system or external dependencies | `build: –Њ–±–љ–Њ–≤–Є—В—М webpack –і–Њ 5.75.0` |
| chore   | Routine maintenance tasks | `chore: –і–Њ–±–∞–≤–Є—В—М .gitignore` |
| ci      | CI/CD configuration changes | `ci: –і–Њ–±–∞–≤–Є—В—М GitHub Actions workflow` |
| docs    | Documentation updates | `docs: –Є—Б–њ—А–∞–≤–Є—В—М –њ—А–Є–Љ–µ—А –≤ API-reference` |
| feat    | New feature | `feat: –і–Њ–±–∞–≤–Є—В—М —Н–љ–і–њ–Њ–Є–љ—В /health` |
| fix     | Bug fix | `fix: –Є—Б–њ—А–∞–≤–Є—В—М –њ–∞—А—Б–Є–љ–≥ –і–∞—В—Л –≤ —Н–Ї—Б–њ–Њ—А—В–µ` |
| perf    | Performance improvement | `perf: –Ї—Н—И–Є—А–Њ–≤–∞—В—М —А–µ–Ј—Г–ї—М—В–∞—В –Ј–∞–њ—А–Њ—Б–∞` |
| refactor| Code change that is not a feature or fix | `refactor: –≤—Л–љ–µ—Б—В–Є –≤–∞–ї–Є–і–∞—Ж–Є—О –≤ –Њ—В–і–µ–ї—М–љ—Л–є –Љ–Њ–і—Г–ї—М` |
| style   | Formatting, whitespace (no code change) | `style: –њ—А–Є–≤–µ—Б—В–Є –Ї Black` |
| test    | Test changes | `test: –і–Њ–±–∞–≤–Є—В—М —В–µ—Б—В—Л –і–ї—П —Б–µ—А–≤–Є—Б–∞ —Н–Ї—Б–њ–Њ—А—В–∞` |
| revert  | Revert a previous commit | `revert: –Њ—В–Ї–∞—В –Ї–Њ–Љ–Љ–Є—В–∞ abc123` |

## Format

- Use lowercase prefix and a short, imperative description after the colon.
- Optionally add scope: `feat(api): –Њ–њ–Є—Б–∞–љ–Є–µ` or `fix(export): –Њ–њ–Є—Б–∞–љ–Є–µ`.
